podman login: Authenticate with a registry. 

podman pull: Download an image from a registry. 

podman push: Upload an image to a registry. 

podman search: Look for images in a registry.



podman pull [OPTIONS] NAME[:TAG|@DIGEST]

podman pull ubuntu:latest



By default, Podman pulls images from the Docker Hub registry. To pull from a different registry, specify the registry's URL:

podman pull quay.io/podman/stable:latest


You can pull specific versions of images using tags or digests:

podman pull ubuntu:20.04
podman pull ubuntu@sha256:45b23dee08af5e43a7fea6c4cf9c25ccf269ee113168c19722f87876677c5cb2



To troubleshoot, use the --debug flag with the podman pull command for detailed output.

